page.title: 08BUNGALOWS IN MYDDLE
page.content: The {Bungalows}in {Myddle}are mostly in {groups.}There's Hillside Close which is for old people. At the other end there's Edge View, Sundorne, Maes Onnen, Fresh Fields, Green Acres and Dymani. The {Bungalows}are quite new there, they have three bedrooms a kitchen a bathroom and a livingroom, they have a nice{garden}at the back and a lawn at the front. Hillside Close has six{Bungalows} which is part of a housing estate, there are 28 houses. Oak Fields is a big {Bungalow} which is for bed and breakfast with many rooms, it has a big garden with a pond. Park Wood is a small {Bungalow, two people live in it. There is a{ {Bungalow} on the farm which is quite big. It has four bedrooms, a kitchen, a living room and it has a large garden. .
